[02:17.11]In his mouth were the remains of fir trees--\n它嘴里还留着冷杉--\n
[02:20.99]the last meal that he had before he fell into the crevasse and broke his back.\n它掉进冰河裂隙折断脊柱之前的最后一顿饭.\n
[02:26.18]The mammoth has now been restored in the Palaeontological Museum in St.Petersburg.\n这头长毛象已被修复,现存于圣彼得堡古生物学博物馆.\n
[02:32.37]Other animals were trapped in tar pits,\n有的动物掉进天然沥青坑里被保存了下来,\n
